[2] OIE - immediate notification
Date: Fri 16 Apr 2021
Source: OIE-WAHIS (World Animal Health Information System) [edited]
https://wahis.oie.int/#/report-info?reportId=32088


Lumpy skin disease, Chinese Taipei
------------------------------
Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Started: 14 Apr 2021
Confirmed: 15 Apr 2021
Reported: 15 Apr 2021
Reason for notification: recurrence
Last occurrence: 30 Sep 2020
Causal agent: lumpy skin disease virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks
Summary of outbreaks
Total outbreaks (1)
Outbreak location 1: Line district, New Taipei
Started: 14 Apr 2021
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered or killed for commercial use / Vaccinated
Cattle / 130 / 8 / 0 / 8 / 0 / 122

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive

Epidemiological comments: Suspected clinical signs were observed at a farm of New Taipei City and reported by the farm to New Taipei City Government Animal Protection and Health Inspection Office on [14 Apr 2021]. Samples were sent to the National Laboratory, Animal Health Research Institute (AHRI), for diagnosis. Lumpy skin disease (LSD) was confirmed by the AHRI on [15 Apr 2021]. The farm has been placed under movement restriction. All suspected cattle were culled, and the rest will be vaccinated against LSD. Cleaning and disinfection are conducted. In addition, there is a total of 5 cattle farms within a 10 km [6.2 mi] radius of the infected farm. One cattle farm within a 3 km [1.9 mi] radius of the infected farm has been placed under movement restriction, and clinical surveillance is being implemented with the remaining 4 cattle farms within a 10 km [6.2 mi] radius of the infected farm. The preventive vaccination for all cattle farms will be conducted in a zone covering 6 counties/cities in northern Taiwan in priority. All of the cattle farms within the country will be inspected, and the cattle will be vaccinated.

Control measures applied in domestic: surveillance within containment and/or the protection zone; disinfestation; zoning; control of vectors; traceability; official disposal of carcasses, by-products, and waste; movement control inside the country; disinfection; quarantine; ante- and post-mortem inspections
Control measures to be applied in domestic: vaccination in response to the outbreak (s)

Control measures applied in wild: vector surveillance

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type: Animal Health Research Institute, Council of Agriculture (national laboratory)
Species / Test / Test date / Result
Cattle / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 15 Apr 2021 / positive
Cattle / gene sequencing / 15 Apr 2021 / positive

